### Coding Standards

#### TypeScript
- Use strict mode. No `any` types.
- Define interfaces for all data shapes. Put them in `src/types/`.
- Use Zod schemas for all input validation (forms and API payloads).
- Use enums from Prisma schema, don't redefine them.

#### API Routes
- All API routes in `src/app/api/`.
- Every route must: validate input with Zod, check authentication, check authorization (role-based), return standard error format, write audit log for mutations.
- Standard error response: `{ success: false, error: { code: string, message: string, field?: string, ref?: string } }`
- Standard success response: `{ success: true, data: T }`
- Use HTTP status codes correctly: 400 validation, 401 auth, 403 forbidden, 404 not found, 409 conflict, 429 rate limit, 500 internal.
- Wrap all database mutations in transactions.

#### Components
- Use Server Components by default. Only add "use client" when the component needs interactivity.
- Every data-displaying component must handle 4 states: loading (skeleton), empty (EmptyState), error (ErrorBanner), success (data).
- Use Tailwind CSS with CSS custom properties for theme colors.
- No inline styles. No `style` prop.
- Component props must be typed with interfaces.

#### Database
- Use Prisma for all database operations.
- Never write raw SQL unless Prisma cannot express the query.
- Use transactions for multi-table mutations.
- Use soft deletes (is_active / archived flags) not hard deletes.
- Always include `created_at` and `updated_at` on every table.
- All audit log writes are append-only. Never update or delete audit entries.

#### Error Handling
- Every API route has a try/catch wrapping the entire handler.
- Client-side: validate on blur + on submit. Show inline errors below fields.
- Server-side: always validate even if client validated. Never trust client input.
- File uploads: check format, size, and virus scan (async).
- Preserve user input on error. Never clear a form after a failed submission.
- Log all errors with structured JSON including error code, user, action, and request ID.

#### Audit Logging
- Every mutation (create, update, delete, status change) writes an audit log entry.
- Audit entries include: user_id, action_type, module, entity_id, old_value, new_value, channel (Web/AI/Slack/System/Cron), success/failure.
- Failed actions are also logged with success=false and error details.

#### Security
- Hash passwords with bcryptjs (cost factor 12).
- JWT access tokens expire in 15 minutes, refresh tokens in 7 days.
- Role-based middleware on every protected API route.
- Sanitize all user input. Escape HTML in comments.
- Never expose internal error details to users. Show friendly messages with a reference code.

### Theme / Design
- Dark theme default. Light theme available via toggle.
- Colors defined as CSS custom properties in globals.css.
- Red (#FF444F) = primary CTA, active states, destructive actions.
- Teal (#85ACB0) = identifiers, codes, links.
- Amber = warnings, pending states.
- Green = success, approved.
- Purple = AI-related content.
- Blue = system information, uploads.
- Typography: DM Sans for UI, JetBrains Mono for codes/timestamps/IDs.
- Every list page follows Pattern A: stats strip → search + quick chips → expandable filter panel → active filter tags → table → pagination.

